    "type": "message",
    "text": "I think it’s pretty fair. The repository has been up for a year and he’s trying to commercialise his work via a blockchain project. It’s quite possible he’ll license it under GPL to stop others from using it freely in practice.\n\nI just thought it’s worth pointing that out here before people spend too much time looking into the project under the assumption that is free to use.\n\n(There’s nothing wrong with protecting your work, but IMO you should make it clear what the conditions are before you start sharing it. I don’t want to be sued for forking the codebase.)",
